  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\neth_getBlockByNumber\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHi, we are using the latest docker Anvil version, and we notice a difference between Hardhat and Anvil behavior when fetching block by number (`eth_getBlockByNumber`) of unmined blocks.\r\n\r\nWhen forking from a specific block number and querying about a block that wasn't mined yet on the fork, Anvil returns the block information from the archive node passed by the `--fork-url` option, while Hardhat returns null.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Code example\r\nthe same code was executed agains Hardhat and anvil forked Ethereum mainnet from block `15006971` without executing any transactions on the fork.\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\n  const provider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider(\"http://127.0.0.1:8545\");\r\n\r\n  const currentBlock = await provider.getBlockNumber();\r\n  console.log(`current block ${currentBlock}`);\r\n\r\n  const blockNumberInFuture = currentBlock + 10;\r\n  const blockInFuture = await provider.getBlockWithTransactions(blockNumberInFuture);\r\n  console.log(`${blockInFuture.transactions.length}  transactions for block ${blockNumberInFuture}`);\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Hardhat output**:\r\n`getBlockWithTransactions` call returns null.\r\n```\r\ncurrent block 15006971\r\nTypeError: Cannot read property 'transactions' of null\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anvil output**:\r\n```\r\ncurrent block 15006971\r\n408 transactions for block 15006981\r\n```\r\nBlock 15006981 had indeed [408 transactions on mainnet](https://etherscan.io/block/15006981)",
